<section class="hero min-h-[40vh] bg-gradient-to-br from-accent/10 to-base-200 rounded-xl mb-10 flex items-center justify-center shadow-lg">
  <div class="text-center">
    <div class="flex justify-center mb-4">
      <div class="bg-accent/20 rounded-full p-4 inline-block">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-12 w-12 text-accent" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8c-1.657 0-3 1.343-3 3 0 1.657 1.343 3 3 3s3-1.343 3-3c0-1.657-1.343-3-3-3zm0 0V5m0 6v6m0 0c-4.418 0-8 1.79-8 4v2h16v-2c0-2.21-3.582-4-8-4z" />
        </svg>
      </div>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-accent mb-2">Good Faith Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-base-content/70 max-w-2xl mx-auto">We foster a space for genuine questions and learning. Here's how we define and uphold good faith on Genderbase.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8 max-w-4xl">
  <div class="prose lg:prose-xl max-w-none">
    <div class="alert bg-base-200 border-l-4 border-accent/60 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-accent" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8c-1.657 0-3 1.343-3 3 0 1.657 1.343 3 3 3s3-1.343 3-3c0-1.657-1.343-3-3-3zm0 0V5m0 6v6m0 0c-4.418 0-8 1.79-8 4v2h16v-2c0-2.21-3.582-4-8-4z" />
      </svg>
      <span>We expect questions to be asked <strong>in good faith</strong>. If they are, we don't require you to get everything right.</span>
    </div>

    <div class="divider my-8 before:bg-accent/20 after:bg-accent/20">What Does "Good Faith" Mean?</div>
    <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 mb-8">
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-accent badge-outline mt-1 whitespace-nowrap text-sm">Curiosity</span> Questions should be asked with genuine curiosity and a sincere desire to learn and understand.</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-accent badge-outline mt-1 whitespace-nowrap text-sm">Respect</span> Approach conversations with respect, honesty, and openness to new information—even if it challenges your beliefs.</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-accent badge-outline mt-1 whitespace-nowrap text-sm">Support</span> We will not respond with hostility to accidental missteps, and will treat you with respect.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="divider my-8 before:bg-accent/20 after:bg-accent/20">What's Allowed</div>
    <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-8">
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-accent badge-outline mt-1 whitespace-nowrap text-sm">Imperfect Language</span> Using outdated, incorrect, or offensive terminology when it's sincerely accidental or based on a lack of knowledge.</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-accent badge-outline mt-1 whitespace-nowrap text-sm">Challenging</span> Respectfully raising disagreements or asking for clarification.</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-accent badge-outline mt-1 whitespace-nowrap text-sm">Basic Questions</span> Asking fundamental questions about gender concepts that might seem obvious to others but are new to you.</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-accent badge-outline mt-1 whitespace-nowrap text-sm">Clarification</span> Requesting explanations or ongoing conversation with your responder.</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-accent badge-outline mt-1 whitespace-nowrap text-sm">Respectful Disagreement</span> Expressing confusion or requesting evidence while remaining open to learning.</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-accent badge-outline mt-1 whitespace-nowrap text-sm">Personal Experience</span> Asking about lived experiences, in a respectful way.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="divider my-8 before:bg-accent/20 after:bg-accent/20">What's Not Allowed</div>
    <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-8">
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-error badge-outline mt-1 whitespace-nowrap text-sm">Trolling</span> Deliberately asking provocative questions designed to upset or anger others.</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-error badge-outline mt-1 whitespace-nowrap text-sm">Sealioning</span> Asking questions in a way that appears civil but is actually intended to harass or waste time.</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-error badge-outline mt-1 whitespace-nowrap text-sm">Debating Identity</span> Challenging your responder's gender identity.</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-error badge-outline mt-1 whitespace-nowrap text-sm">Repeated Violations</span> Continuing to use harmful language after being corrected.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="divider my-8 before:bg-accent/20 after:bg-accent/20">If Your Question Is Closed</div>
    <p class="mb-8">If your question is closed due to violation of this policy, you will be able to appeal <strong>once</strong>. Responders will evaluate your appeal and if it is accepted, your question will be reopened. You may be assigned a new responder.</p>

    <div class="divider my-8 before:bg-accent/20 after:bg-accent/20">How We Evaluate Good Faith</div>
    <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-8">
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-accent badge-outline mt-1 whitespace-nowrap text-sm">Language & Tone</span> The language and tone of the question.</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-accent badge-outline mt-1 whitespace-nowrap text-sm">Engagement</span> Whether the person engages respectfully with answers and corrections.</li>
      <li class="bg-base-200 rounded-xl p-4 shadow flex items-start gap-3"><span class="badge badge-accent badge-outline mt-1 whitespace-nowrap text-sm">Willingness</span> Willingness to learn and adjust language when informed.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="alert bg-base-200 border-l-4 border-accent/60 mb-8 flex items-center gap-3">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-6 w-6 text-accent" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8c-1.657 0-3 1.343-3 3 0 1.657 1.343 3 3 3s3-1.343 3-3c0-1.657-1.343-3-3-3zm0 0V5m0 6v6m0 0c-4.418 0-8 1.79-8 4v2h16v-2c0-2.21-3.582-4-8-4z" />
      </svg>
      <span>We reserve the right to close questions that are not asked in good faith without answering. Our responders are human and do not deserve to be harassed.</span>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-8">Our goal is to maintain Genderbase as a space where people can learn about gender identity and expression without fear, while ensuring the community remains respectful and supportive.</p>

    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center mt-10">
      <%= link_to "About Genderbase", home_about_path, class: "btn btn-primary btn-lg shadow" %>
      <%= link_to "Help & Support", home_support_path, class: "btn btn-outline btn-lg shadow" %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>